      "date": "2017-06-02 19:33:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI am not against this patch, but I am wondering how we can end up having problems, since ll_dentry_init_security() will call security_dentry_init_security() only if selinux_is_enabled() returns != 0.\nDoes it mean selinux_is_enabled() can return != 0 when CONFIG_SECURITY is not defined?",
